<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/1341474-why-is-it-called-beneath-the-wheel">why is it called &quot;Beneath the wheel&quot; ?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_1341474'><a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F25905.Beneath_the_Wheel">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/1341474-why-is-it-called-beneath-the-wheel">3 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/1341474-why-is-it-called-beneath-the-wheel">Add your answer</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/57220472-luca-szabo"><img alt="" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_100x100-259587f1619f5253426a4fa6fb508831.png" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/57220472-luca-szabo">Luca Szabo</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">A teacher of Hans&apos; (the protagonist of the novel) warns Hans, when he begins to neglect his schoolwork, that he is in danger of being &quot;crushed beneath<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">A teacher of Hans' (the protagonist of the novel) warns Hans, when he begins to neglect his schoolwork, that he is in danger of being "crushed beneath the wheel," a metaphor for saying that if Hans does not apply himself robotically to his school work, he will suffer. Of course, the main concept of the novel is realizing the value of succeeding in a school compared to that of living soulfully and poetically, is inferior.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerFooter'>

