<span id="freeTextContainer15911659160677221358">This is only Hesse&apos;s second novel and not his best. It is somewhat autobiographical and, like many of the author&apos;s novels, is a tale of a young man&apos;s disillusionment, rebellion and self-discovery. My notes on the book from the time of reading summarize it as follows: &quot;Raised without a mother and crushed by the ordered, competitive, masculine world&apos;s expectations. The destruction of a young spirit.&quot;</span>
  <span id="freeText15911659160677221358" style="display:none">This is only Hesse's second novel and not his best. It is somewhat autobiographical and, like many of the author's novels, is a tale of a young man's disillusionment, rebellion and self-discovery. My notes on the book from the time of reading summarize it as follows: "Raised without a mother and crushed by the ordered, competitive, masculine world's expectations. The destruction of a young spirit."</span>
