<div id="review_2893061277" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2893061277" />
    <a title="Bohdan Pechenyak" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/13542582-bohdan-pechenyak"><img alt="Bohdan Pechenyak" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1520453591p2/13542582.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2893061277?book_show_action=true">Jul 13, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Bohdan Pechenyak" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Bohdan Pechenyak" href="/user/show/13542582-bohdan-pechenyak">Bohdan Pechenyak</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/13542582-bohdan-pechenyak?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/13542582-bohdan-pechenyak?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2893061277" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18143739461139673977">One of the earlier Hesse’s novels, touching on his usual themes of academic ambition, life of the mind, artistic vision, the oppressive social system, including the academia, the employment, the cultural mores etc. It is quite easy to get caught beneath the heavy ever-turning wheel of the system, especially for a sensitive spirit unprepared to the practical vagaries of life. Not Hesse’s best or most gripping, but a clear stepping stone toward later novels. </span>

          </span>
        </div>


