    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_4069130256" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4069130256" />
    <a title="James Mayo" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/70030198-james-mayo"><img alt="James Mayo" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4069130256?book_show_action=true">Jun 20, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="James Mayo" class="user" itemprop="url" name="James Mayo" href="/user/show/70030198-james-mayo">James Mayo</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Mass Market Paperback 9780553058598" href="/book/show/25909.Beneath_the_Wheel">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4069130256" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer380643799090562981">After reading siddhartha and Steppenwolf over a year ago, and then returning recently to read Demian, I thought it best to find a new Hesse book for my backpacking trip. Each night I found a little energy left to turn on my headlamp and read Beneath the Wheel. Sadly, it was the least enjoyable of my Hesse readings. I got so detached and it truly did feel more autobiographical than a story for everyone. <br/><br/>I recently graduated from college but felt little connection because I wasn’t the genius Hans </span>
  <span id="freeText380643799090562981" style="display:none">After reading siddhartha and Steppenwolf over a year ago, and then returning recently to read Demian, I thought it best to find a new Hesse book for my backpacking trip. Each night I found a little energy left to turn on my headlamp and read Beneath the Wheel. Sadly, it was the least enjoyable of my Hesse readings. I got so detached and it truly did feel more autobiographical than a story for everyone. <br /><br />I recently graduated from college but felt little connection because I wasn’t the genius Hans was in the story. I understood the pressure education puts on students but I never felt the same dramatic effects. <br /><br />Furthermore, it was dated, and not being German, proved to make my mental picturing a bit difficult. By that I mean there were a lot of spruces and a river but that was about it. There are many old novels that do well to tell a story of some mutual human feeling and it doesn’t matter the year it was written in. However, this story felt distant and because of that so did the society and culture Hans was in. <br /><br />I’ll return to Hesse because he really is special when he is on. However, I’m ready for something other than a coming of age story. </span>
  <a data-text-id="380643799090562981" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

